# ── CHAIN privacy firewall ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# The repo ships the MECHANISM, never your data. CHAIN owns ONE writable root,
# chain_home (default ~/.chain, outside the repo). Your sources and canon are
# referenced in place and never copied here. If any of these ever show up tracked,
# stop and check before committing.

# Your real, path-bearing config (copy of chain.config.example.yaml)
chain.config.local.yaml
*.config.local.yaml

# Personal-identifier denylist read by the local pre-commit firewall hook
*denylist.local.txt

# chain_home when kept local (library, learned state, disposable workspace, cache).
# The default ~/.chain lives outside the repo; this covers the demo's ./.chain too.
.chain/

# The SYNTHETIC demo home is committed on purpose so the repo runs with no real data.
!examples/demo-home/
!examples/demo-home/**

# Credentials / session
.env
*.secret
credentials*.json
session*.json

# ── ordinary noise ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.DS_Store
*.egg-info/
.venv/
